  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hey,\r\nI noticed that the call to `finalize()` in FinalizableCrowdsale.sol is guarded by the modifier `onlyOwner`.\r\nUnless this finalizable action is meant to be optional, I can't really see any reason for it not to be open to the public to call to avoid the owner being able to block the token contracts state from progressing if needed.\r\nFor example, in the derived RefundableCrowdsale.sol crowdsale contributors can't process their refunds until the crowdsale has been finalized, which only the owner could do - hence the owner could block refunds (note - they would also block themselves from collecting the wallet ether).\r\nThoughts? Happy to submit a PR if consensus is that this should be changed.\r\nThanks,\r\nAdam",
