    "body": "It is usually for security reasons that we only allow an owner to trigger these administrative tasks, so that an attacker cannot use the function.\r\n\r\nThat said, I see how it can be an issue. It would be ok if the owner was incentivized to call `finalize`, but in `RefundableCrowdsale`, for example, they are only incentivized when the crowdsale was successful, and there is not much incentive to give people their refunds.\r\n\r\nI'd like to hear what others think about this too.",
