    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In a way, the whole Crowdsale thing relies on trusting that the token emitter is going to follow up with their plans to build a strong network around them, so I'd argue that this is a minor detail compared to the rest.\r\n\r\nIn this particular case, though, the problem with letting anyone call `finalize` is that it will prevent any further minting of new tokens, which the owner might want to do right after the sale to ensure that the team and early contributors get their agreed upon shares.",
