    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I def. see your point, but a couple of other observations:\r\n1) in the above, any action the owner may want to take after the sale finishes should be a part of the finalize function I think - the function doesn't take arguments so would need to encode all of the logic upfront but this doesn't seem unreasonable to maintain a trustless nature.\r\n2) if finalize needs to remain as callable only by the owner I wonder whether the refundable crowdsale contract should be implemented outside of the finalizable framework so that refunds can remain trustless (so be based purely on whether a crowdsale has completed, and if so whether or not it met its stated goal).",
